hpicfDot1xMIB.name: hpicfDot1xMIB

revisions.description: Added new MIB object for initial role that can be configured per port: hpicfDot1xPaePortInitialRole

Added new MIB objects for port-access critical/open auth commands hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthVoiceVid, hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthDataVid, hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthUserRole, hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthVoiceVid, hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthDataVid, hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthUserRole
Added object hpicfDot1xAuthEnforceCacheReauth and corresponding compliance.
Added object hpicfDot1x2010 and corresponding compliance.

Added objects hpicfDot1xAuthSessionRoleName and hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup1. Added initialRole and heldInitialRoleFailed to hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaeState. Added applyInitialRole to hpicfDot1xSMAuthBackendAuthState. Added compliance hpicfDot1xCompliance11. Updated description for objects hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthPeriod, hpicfDot1xAuthAuthVid, hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthVid, and hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthPeriod.
Added object hpicfDot1xPaePortSpeedVSA, compliance hpicfDot1xCompliance9 and group hpicfDot1xPaeAuthSessionGroup1 .
Added description for hpicfDot1xPaePortMBV object in HpicfDot1xPaePortEntry.
Added description for hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeout object in HpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigEntry.
Added two more values for hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaeState. Added hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthPeriod.
Added two more values for hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaeState.

hpicfDot1xMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfDot1xMIB.description: This MIB module contains the definitions of Managed Objects for HP extensions to IEEE 802.1X. This MIB supplements the IEEE 802.1X MIB to provide a mechanism by which to configure and retrieve status on shared-media ports, such as in wireless access points or multi-supplicant mode on HP switches/routers.

hpicfDot1xPaePortEntry.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortEntry
hpicfDot1xPaePortEntry.description: The fields in these entries will be used to supplement 'dot1xPaePortEntry'.

hpicfDot1xPaePortAuth.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortAuth
hpicfDot1xPaePortAuth.description: This object allows enable/disable authenticator functionality on a port.

hpicfDot1xPaePortSupp.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortSupp
hpicfDot1xPaePortSupp.description: This object allows enable/disable supplicant functionality on a port.

hpicfDot1xPaePortMixed.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortMixed
hpicfDot1xPaePortMixed.description: This object allows enable/disable guests on ports with authenticated clients.

hpicfDot1xPaePortSpeedVSA.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortSpeedVSA
hpicfDot1xPaePortSpeedVSA.description: This object allows enable or disable port speed VSA processing on a port.

hpicfDot1xPaePortMBV.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortMBV
hpicfDot1xPaePortMBV.description: This object enables and disables the MAC-based VLANs feature on the port.

hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthVoiceVid.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthVoiceVid
hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthVoiceVid.description: The VLANID which is being assinged as a critical-auth voice vlan.

hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthDataVid.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthDataVid
hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthDataVid.description: The VLANID which is being assinged as a critical-auth data vlan.

hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthUserRole.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthUserRole
hpicfDot1xPaePortCritAuthUserRole.description: This object specifies the user role of the client for critical-auth.

hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthVoiceVid.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthVoiceVid
hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthVoiceVid.description: The VLANID which is being assinged as a open-auth voice vlan.

hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthDataVid.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthDataVid
hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthDataVid.description: The VLANID which is being assinged as a open-auth data vlan.

hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthUserRole.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthUserRole
hpicfDot1xPaePortOpenAuthUserRole.description: This object specifies the user role of the client for open-auth.

hpicfDot1xPaePortInitialRole.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortInitialRole
hpicfDot1xPaePortInitialRole.description: This object specifies the initial role that is configured for a port.

hpicfDot1x2010.name: hpicfDot1x2010
hpicfDot1x2010.description: The administrative enable dot1x 2010 compliance support gobally for authenticator and supplicant.

hpicfDot1xAuthConfigEntry.name: hpicfDot1xAuthConfigEntry
hpicfDot1xAuthConfigEntry.description: The fields in these entries will be used to supplement 'dot1xAuthConfigEntry'.

hpicfDot1xAuthAuthVid.name: hpicfDot1xAuthAuthVid
hpicfDot1xAuthAuthVid.description: This object configures the PVID for the authorized 802.1x port. When hpSwitchAutzUserRoleEnabled is true, this value may be superseded by the value of hpSwitchAutzUserRoleVlanId or hpSwitchAutzUserRoleVlanName from the client's assigned role.

hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthVid.name: hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthVid
hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthVid.description: This object configures the PVID for the unauthorized 802.1x port. When hpSwitchAutzUserRoleEnabled is true, this value may be superseded by the value of hpSwitchAutzUserRoleVlanId or hpSwitchAutzUserRoleVlanName from the role identified by hpSwitchAutzUserRoleInitialRoleName.

hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthPeriod.name: hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthPeriod
hpicfDot1xAuthUnauthPeriod.description: This objects configures the period of time, in seconds, which the authenticator will wait for authentication before transitioning to guest VLAN mode, or assigning the role identified by hpSwitchAutzUserRoleInitialRoleName when hpSwitchAutzUserRoleEnabled is true.

hpicfDot1xAuthClientLimit.name: hpicfDot1xAuthClientLimit
hpicfDot1xAuthClientLimit.description: *************THIS OBJECT IS DEPRECATED ********** The maximum number of authenticated clients to allow on the port.

hpicfDot1xAuthLogoffPeriod.name: hpicfDot1xAuthLogoffPeriod
hpicfDot1xAuthLogoffPeriod.description: Specifies the period, in seconds, at which an authenticated client will be considered unauthenticated for a lack of activity (i.e. traffic originating from client).

hpicfDot1xAuthClientLimit2.name: hpicfDot1xAuthClientLimit2
hpicfDot1xAuthClientLimit2.description: The maximum number of authenticated clients to allow on the port if greater than 0. If 0 then authenticator controls port as a single entity - no client limit.

hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthPeriod.name: hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthPeriod
hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthPeriod.description: The value indicates the period in seconds, during which cached reauthentication is allowed on the port. If value is zero then the period of cached reauthentication is unlimited.

hpicfDot1xAuthEnforceCacheReauth.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEnforceCacheReauth
hpicfDot1xAuthEnforceCacheReauth.description: Setting this attribute TRUE(1) will allow cached reauthentication when server-timeout is configured lesser than radius connection timeout or when client initiates authentication before the radius connection timeout during reauthentication.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigTable.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigTable
hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration and basic status objects for Authenticator PAEs associated with each shared-media port.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigEntry.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigEntry
hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaePort.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaePort
hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaePort.description: The interface index associated with this Authenticator PAE. On wired HP products the interface index is the physical port. On wireless products it is the instance (whether real or virtual) of an AP.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthMacAddr.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthMacAddr
hpicfDot1xSMAuthMacAddr.description: The 48-bit IEEE media access control address of The supplicant associated with this Authenticator PAE.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthInitialize.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthInitialize
hpicfDot1xSMAuthInitialize.description: The initialization control for this Authenticator PAE. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the PAE to be initialized. The attribute value reverts to FALSE once initialization has completed.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthReauthenticate.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthReauthenticate
hpicfDot1xSMAuthReauthenticate.description: The reauthentication control for this Authenticator PAE. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Authenticator PAE state machine for the Port to reauthenticate the Supplicant. Setting this attribute FALSE has no effect. This attribute always returns FALSE when it is read.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaeState.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaeState
hpicfDot1xSMAuthPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthBackendAuthState.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthBackendAuthState
hpicfDot1xSMAuthBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthPeriod.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthPeriod
hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine. When hpSwitchAutzUserRoleEnabled is true, this value will be superseded by the value of hpSwitchAutzUserRoleReauthPeriod from the client's assigned role.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthEnabled.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthEnabled
hpicfDot1xSMAuthReAuthEnabled.description: The enable/disable control used by the Reauthentication Timer state machine (8.5.5.1).

hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeout.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeout
hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeout.description: Specifies the RADIUS Server set session timeout for reauthentication of the user. When ST = 0, user gets reauthenticated at reauth-period secs, ST < 60 it is set to 60 secs and then user is reauthenticated, ST > 60 user is reauthenticated at ST secs.

hpicfDot1xAuthDiagTable.name: hpicfDot1xAuthDiagTable
hpicfDot1xAuthDiagTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

hpicfDot1xAuthDiagEntry.name: hpicfDot1xAuthDiagEntry
hpicfDot1xAuthDiagEntry.description: The diagnostic information for an Authenticator PAE.

hpicfDot1xAuthNumberOfSuccessAuthenticat.name: hpicfDot1xAuthNumberOfSuccessAuthentication
hpicfDot1xAuthNumberOfSuccessAuthenticat.description: Counts the number of times that authenticator received an EAP-Success message from Authentication Server. Indicates that Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

hpicfDot1xAuthNumberOfFailedAuthenticati.name: hpicfDot1xAuthNumberOfFailedAuthentication
hpicfDot1xAuthNumberOfFailedAuthenticati.description: Counts the number of times that authenticator received an EAP-Failure message from Authentication Server. Indicates that Supplicant has failed to authenticate to the Authentication Server.

hpicfDot1xAuthStatsTable.name: hpicfDot1xAuthStatsTable
hpicfDot1xAuthStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE's associated with each shared-media Port.

hpicfDot1xAuthStatsEntry.name: hpicfDot1xAuthStatsEntry
hpicfDot1xAuthStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

hpicfDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognized.

hpicfDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

hpicfDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.name: hpicfDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion
hpicfDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

hpicfDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.name: hpicfDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource
hpicfDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the session statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE's associated with each shared-media Port.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics information for an Authenticator PAE. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session on each port where there is no session currently active.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionPerPAECountersEnabl.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionPerPAECountersEnabled
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionPerPAECountersEnabl.description: Specifies whether individualized PAE octet and frame counts are supported. If TRUE then system is capable of maintaining separate counter sets for each, of possibly many, Authenticator PAE instance on a port. If FALSE then system is incapable of maintaining separate counter sets. Frame and octet counter values returned are an aggregate of all PAE sessions on the port.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received in user data frames during the session.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted in user data frames during the session.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.description: The number of user data frames received during the session.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted during the session.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionId.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionId
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionTime.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionTime
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in seconds.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStartTime.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStartTime
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStartTime.description: This object contains the value of sysUpTime at the time Supplicant was successfully authenticated.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStopTime.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStopTime
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStopTime.description: This object contains the value of sysUpTime at the time an authenticated Supplicant was de-authenticated, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff, reauthentication period expiration, or forced asynchronous reauthentication.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionInactiveTime.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionInactiveTime
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionInactiveTime.description: This time (in seconds) since last user data frames, either received or transmitted, were observed.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionUserName.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionUserName
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionIsForwarding.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionIsForwarding
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionIsForwarding.description: Specifies whether traffic originating from Supplicant PAE is being forwarded by Authenticator PAE. If TRUE, then Authenticator is forwarding Supplicant's traffic If FALSE, then Authenticator is not forwarding (blocking) Supplicant's traffic.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionVid.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionVid
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionVid.description: The PVID on which user data frames are being forwarded.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionRoleName.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionRoleName
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionRoleName.description: When hpSwitchAutzUserRoleEnabled is true, specifies the user role of the client assigned to the Supplicant PAE.

hpicfDot1xAuthAllowGvrpVlans.name: hpicfDot1xAuthAllowGvrpVlans
hpicfDot1xAuthAllowGvrpVlans.description: This object allows enable/disable the use of RADIUS-assigned dynamic (GVRP) VLANs.

hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthDelay.name: hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthDelay
hpicfDot1xAuthCachedReauthDelay.description: The value indicates the period in seconds, during which all reauthentications will be suppressed after a cached reauthentication.

hpicfDot1xSuppConfigEntry.name: hpicfDot1xSuppConfigEntry
hpicfDot1xSuppConfigEntry.description: The fields in these entries will be used to supplement 'dot1xSuppConfigEntry'.

hpicfDot1xSuppConfigIdentity.name: hpicfDot1xSuppConfigIdentity
hpicfDot1xSuppConfigIdentity.description: This object can be used to set/get the identity 802.1x supplicant supplies to its authenticator.

hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPassword.name: hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPassword
hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPassword.description: This object can be used to set the password the supplicant uses for MD5 authentication.

hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPasswordEncrypted.name: hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPasswordEncrypted
hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPasswordEncrypted.description: The encrypted form of the password used by supplicant for MD5 authentication. This object may only be read or written when hpSwitchAuthenticationEncryptCredentialsMethod is set to a value other than none(0). At most one of hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPassword and hpicfDot1xSuppConfigPasswordEncrypted may be set in any transaction. This object should only be written with an encrypted password previously read from a compatible HP Networking device.

hpicfDot1xPaePortGroup.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortGroup
hpicfDot1xPaePortGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic administrative control over Authenticator PAE and Supplicant PAE in system.

hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup.name: hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup
hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup.description: ********* THIS GROUP IS DEPRECATED ********* A collection of objects providing basic configuration control of over Authenticator PAEs.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigGroup.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigGroup
hpicfDot1xSMAuthConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic status and configuration control over Authenticator PAEs running on a shared-media port.

hpicfDot1xAuthDiagGroup.name: hpicfDot1xAuthDiagGroup
hpicfDot1xAuthDiagGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic diagnostic Information over Authenticator PAEs.

hpicfDot1xAuthStatsGroup.name: hpicfDot1xAuthStatsGroup
hpicfDot1xAuthStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistics about Authenticator PAEs running on a shared-media port.

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistics about the current, or last sessions for Authenticator PAEs running on a shared-media port.

hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup2.name: hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup2
hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing basic configuration control of over Authenticator PAEs.

hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup3.description: A collection of objects providing basic configuration control of over Authenticator PAEs.

hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup4.description: A collection of objects providing basic configuration control of over Authenticator PAEs.

hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup5.name: hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup5
hpicfDot1xAuthConfigGroup5.description: A collection of objects providing basic configuration control of over Authenticator PAEs.

hpicfDot1xSuppConfigGroup.name: hpicfDot1xSuppConfigGroup
hpicfDot1xSuppConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic configuration of the 802.1x supplicant.

hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeoutGroup.name: hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeoutGroup
hpicfDot1xSMAuthSessionTimeoutGroup.description: A collection of objects providing RADIUS server set session timeout for user reauthentication

hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup1.name: hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup1
hpicfDot1xAuthSessionStatsGroup1.description: A collection of objects providing statistics about the current, or last sessions for Authenticator PAEs running on a shared-media port.

hpicfDot1xSystemGroup.name: hpicfDot1xSystemGroup
hpicfDot1xSystemGroup.description: A collection of objects providing dot1x 2010 support for authenticator and supplicant.

hpicfDot1xPaePortGroup1.name: hpicfDot1xPaePortGroup1
hpicfDot1xPaePortGroup1.description: A collection of objects providing configuration support for critial/open auth vlan.
